<br>
When I go on a Keal raid.  What's in it for me? I get faction (well, ok, faction is maxxed, but I still like the rush).  Any drop (if it happens) is a bonus.<br>
<br>
When I help on a General raid, when I help kill Lucan, when I go on a CoM raid, or any other epic encounter step. What's in it for me? Satisfaction of knowing someone is closer to their epic.<br>
<br>
When I go Dungeon crawling.  What's in it for me?  Learning the zone or showing someone else the zone. Again.. Satisfaction for me.. Enjoyment for me..<br>
<br>
When I go on an xp camp. What's in it for me? XP.  Drops are a bonus.<br>
<br>
When a great drop happens and someone else gets it.  What's in it for me? Joy in knowing that they got a great drop.  I get enjoyment knowing they must feel how I would feel if I got the drop. Thats what's in it for me.<br>
<br>
If I have the time, and am not currently doing something else.. I help because I enjoy helping.. That's what's in it for me.<br>
<br>
Why would anyone do anything that they don't get something in return.&lt; Rhetorical, so I didn't use a question mark. &gt;  It is up to us all as individuals to decide what we consider fair compensation.<br>
<br>
I think we have all been signed up for a raid that had to be canceled because Class X didn't show up. And yes, that is a disappointment. But hey, Shit Happens.<br>
<br>
I think we have all signed up for raid, and not been on the list to go... again Shit Happens.<br>
<br>
This is a (rather fun) game.  We all play for enjoyment. We all find enjoyment in different ways. Enjoyment is probably the biggest selfish reason for playing the game.<br>
<br>
Dest - You implied that not going to raid because you have other plans is a BAD thing.  I disagree.  You implied that a person saying they are busy is an excuse.  I disagree. <br>
<br>
Of course, all my above statements are generalizations. My friends know that I will drop what I am doing to help them, if it is possible. If it is not possible, they in turn, will undestand and not stand in judgement against me.  I have no plans for doing my epic, yet I will continue to help others... not because I will look bad if and when I don't have time to help... but because I enjoy helping.<br>
<br>
This was not meant as a flame on anyone.  I agree with what Dest posts most of the time. This time, I don't (or didn't understand his post).<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
