<br>
My point is this. I will use myself as an example and this is totally made up and not directed any one, but I am sure you will be able to see the correlation.<br>
<br>
I go to Dragon Nec to help farm some decent weapons for some tank friends. There is one drop in the entire zone that I can use, but I don't need it because I have a hiero cloak. Why do I go? To help them out. <br>
<br>
The next day I post about wanting to kill the Scorpion dude for one of my epic parts. Give a weeks notice. I get there and only a few people there, mostly casters. I ask ubertank_01 are you going to come help with the scorpion? Ubertank_01 says Not today, I think I want to see if I can get into a guard group and try to get a lammy. I cancel my raid because of lack of tanks. <br>
<br>
Now if one of the side drops of the Scorpion were Uberweapon_15 the tank probably would have shown up.<br>
<br>
Example two: Level 54 Shaman hasn't gone on any raids to help out with epics before. You Schedule a raid to go to The Hole for your chanter drop. Shammy signs up and also post's since we are going to be near there. Can we go kill the guy for my epic also. <br>
<br>
Personally that would have been in my plan to do any way, because they are close. But it's also a situation where I know that had it been another mob. He wouldn't have shown up.<br>
<br>
Again these are just made up situations. But do you see my point? <br>
<br>
Dest<br>
