<br>
I have not had the time commitment for raids for a few months.  I have recently started having more time (Fall softball leagues are almost over, etc.) so I have started signing up for raids more.  During the summer, I didn't go on any raids (softball 3 nights a week, regular group once a week, etc.).  <br>
<br>
Your shaman example could be similar to my time allotment.. he/she just didn't have time, and coincidentally, had time when you scheduled your raid, so tryed a tag along raid. /shrug.<br>
<br>
Your tank example does smell bad IMHO.  I guess I would be offended at the tank as well, but would just lower my priority on helping that tank in the future.  Even still, he may have already made a commitment to the guard group to be a replacement and he just worded his reply bad /shrug<br>
<br>
Also, I have noticed that you have been doing RBL raids, and I bet if you (or Shabbate, if you don't like leading raids and you could convince her) organized a raid, your turnout would be great.  I know I would sign up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  err. .given a weeks notice and not on Mondays or Tuesdays or Fridays or Sundays assuming I am in town. hehe.  I know my tank is sorta low for deep hole raids (and I am lacking in resist gear) but a good cleric can keep any tank alive.. or at least rez em back =P<br>
<br>
My point was just that, it may seem like they are not helping, but in fact they may have other commitments. And I for one, believe in honoring my commitments.  If I recieve a tell in game asking for my assistance, and I have to answer 'Sorry, but I can't right now', I don't think it is right that a person immediatley assumes I am an ass that doesn't help anyone.  I can't even count the times I received GG pleas from people, and when I tell them 'Sorry, I am helping a friend right now' gotten /rude type responses from the person. Oh well, just another to add to my list /shrug<br>
<br>
Oh well.  I guess we probably both see each others point, I just hope that people consider that 'I can't right now' or 'I can't that night' is an OK response.<br>
<br>
